cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.HC 

The paper focuses on facial expression recognition algorithms and proposes a novel deep learning approach to address dataset bias. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the conditional probability distributions between source and target datasets, indicating a potential focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of lab-controlled datasets and real-world databases suggests a potential focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
